								"type": "wysiwyg_basic",
								"html": "<div class=\"rounded p-6 gap-3 mt-3 bg-secondary-200 text-light\" style=\"color:#FFFFFF;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;\">\n\t&nbsp;\n</p>\n\n<h2><a href=\"https://give.salvationarmycarolinas.org/event/gameday-cafe-2026/e759258/register/new/select-tickets\" class=\"btn btn-light gap-1 mt-2\">Sponsor Event</a></h2>\n\n<h2><a href=\"https://give.salvationarmycarolinas.org/event/gameday-cafe-2026/e759258/register/new/select-tickets\" class=\"btn btn-light gap-1 mt-2\">Purchase Tickets</a></h2>\n\n<h2>The Story Behind the Songbird Cafe' &amp; GameDay Cafe'</h2>\n\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"font-size:20px;\">The <strong>Songbird Café </strong>began with a simple but powerful vision shared by <strong>Jimmy Stevenson</strong> of Southern Way Catering and <strong>Ricky Wright</strong>, formerly with Hootie &amp; the Blowfish. Together, they imagined an intimate evening of music — a space where stories, songwriting, and soulful performances could take center stage.</span>\n</p>\n\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Their inspiration came from the iconic <strong>Bluebird Café</strong>, the world-renowned 90-seat listening room tucked inside a modest Nashville strip mall. Over the years, its stage has launched and hosted legendary artists including <strong>Garth Brooks, Keith Urban, Mary Chapin Carpenter, Kris Kristofferson, Carole King, Faith Hill, Vince Gill, and Taylor Swift</strong>, among many others.</span>\n</p>\n\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"font-size:20px;\">After months of planning, collaboration, and determination, that vision became a reality. In <strong>October 2002</strong>, the very first Songbird Café took place, featuring unforgettable performances by <strong>Mark Bryan, Patrick Davis, Phillip Lammonds, and Edwin McCain</strong>. What began as a single evening of music quickly became a beloved annual tradition.</span>\n</p>\n\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"font-size:20px;\">More than two decades later, Songbird Café continues to thrive. <strong>October 2026 will&nbsp;mark&nbsp;the 24th&nbsp;annual Songbird Café,</strong> a milestone that reflects its lasting impact on both the Midlands music scene and the charitable community it serves.</span>\n</p>\n\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Building on that legacy, <strong>GameDay Café</strong> debuted in May 2024 as the high-energy, springtime sister event to Songbird Café. Hosted at <strong>Williams-Brice Stadium</strong>, GameDay Café captures the electric atmosphere, shared pride, and sense of community that fans feel inside the stadium on game day — even outside football season. Live music and storytelling take center stage in a setting that is both iconic and uniquely energizing. <strong>May 14, 2026 will mark the 3rd annual GameDay Café,</strong> solidifying its place as a signature event.</span>\n</p>\n\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Over the years, Songbird Café and GameDay Café stages have been graced by an extraordinary lineup of artists, including <strong>Darius Rucker, Kevin Kinney, Ed Roland, Hobart Trotter, Glen Phillips, Tift Merritt, Radney Foster, Don Dixon, Ken Block &amp; Andrew Copeland, Emerson Hart, Angie Aparo</strong>, and many more — each bringing their unique voice and story to our community.</span>\n</p>\n\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Beyond the music,<strong> Songbird Café and GameDay Café were created with purpose</strong>. For more than 20 years, these events have raised over <strong>$2 million</strong> in support of local charities throughout the Midlands, directly strengthening organizations that serve our neighbors in meaningful ways.</span>\n</p>\n\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"font-size:20px;\">This impact would not be possible without the unwavering generosity of our sponsors, partners, and volunteers. Their support — combined with the extraordinary talent on our&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">stages — has allowed these events to become both cultural touchstones and powerful engines of charitable giving.</span>\n</p>\n\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"font-size:20px;\">We invite you to continue this legacy with us. By joining the Songbird Café and GameDay Café family, you become part of a tradition that celebrates music, community, and compassion — creating moments that resonate far beyond the stage and into the heart of our Midlands community.</span>\n</p>\n\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"font-size:20px;\"></span>\n</p>\n\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Below is a list of The Songbird Cafes’ and&nbsp;the GameDay Cafe’s, many singers, songwriters, producers, and everything else in between!</span>\n</p></div>",
								"content": "<div class=\"rounded p-6 gap-3 mt-3 bg-secondary-200 text-light\" style=\"color:#FFFFFF;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;\">\n\t&nbsp;\n</p>\n\n<h2><a href=\"https://give.salvationarmycarolinas.org/event/gameday-cafe-2026/e759258/register/new/select-tickets\" class=\"btn btn-light gap-1 mt-2\">Sponsor Event</a></h2>\n\n<h2><a href=\"https://give.salvationarmycarolinas.org/event/gameday-cafe-2026/e759258/register/new/select-tickets\" class=\"btn btn-light gap-1 mt-2\">Purchase Tickets</a></h2>\n\n<h2>The Story Behind the Songbird Cafe' &amp; GameDay Cafe'</h2>\n\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"font-size:20px;\">The <strong>Songbird Café </strong>began with a simple but powerful vision shared by <strong>Jimmy Stevenson</strong> of Southern Way Catering and <strong>Ricky Wright</strong>, formerly with Hootie &amp; the Blowfish. Together, they imagined an intimate evening of music — a space where stories, songwriting, and soulful performances could take center stage.</span>\n</p>\n\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Their inspiration came from the iconic <strong>Bluebird Café</strong>, the world-renowned 90-seat listening room tucked inside a modest Nashville strip mall. Over the years, its stage has launched and hosted legendary artists including <strong>Garth Brooks, Keith Urban, Mary Chapin Carpenter, Kris Kristofferson, Carole King, Faith Hill, Vince Gill, and Taylor Swift</strong>, among many others.</span>\n</p>\n\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"font-size:20px;\">After months of planning, collaboration, and determination, that vision became a reality. In <strong>October 2002</strong>, the very first Songbird Café took place, featuring unforgettable performances by <strong>Mark Bryan, Patrick Davis, Phillip Lammonds, and Edwin McCain</strong>. What began as a single evening of music quickly became a beloved annual tradition.</span>\n</p>\n\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"font-size:20px;\">More than two decades later, Songbird Café continues to thrive. <strong>October 2026 will&nbsp;mark&nbsp;the 24th&nbsp;annual Songbird Café,</strong> a milestone that reflects its lasting impact on both the Midlands music scene and the charitable community it serves.</span>\n</p>\n\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Building on that legacy, <strong>GameDay Café</strong> debuted in May 2024 as the high-energy, springtime sister event to Songbird Café. Hosted at <strong>Williams-Brice Stadium</strong>, GameDay Café captures the electric atmosphere, shared pride, and sense of community that fans feel inside the stadium on game day — even outside football season. Live music and storytelling take center stage in a setting that is both iconic and uniquely energizing. <strong>May 14, 2026 will mark the 3rd annual GameDay Café,</strong> solidifying its place as a signature event.</span>\n</p>\n\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Over the years, Songbird Café and GameDay Café stages have been graced by an extraordinary lineup of artists, including <strong>Darius Rucker, Kevin Kinney, Ed Roland, Hobart Trotter, Glen Phillips, Tift Merritt, Radney Foster, Don Dixon, Ken Block &amp; Andrew Copeland, Emerson Hart, Angie Aparo</strong>, and many more — each bringing their unique voice and story to our community.</span>\n</p>\n\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Beyond the music,<strong> Songbird Café and GameDay Café were created with purpose</strong>. For more than 20 years, these events have raised over <strong>$2 million</strong> in support of local charities throughout the Midlands, directly strengthening organizations that serve our neighbors in meaningful ways.</span>\n</p>\n\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"font-size:20px;\">This impact would not be possible without the unwavering generosity of our sponsors, partners, and volunteers. Their support — combined with the extraordinary talent on our&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">stages — has allowed these events to become both cultural touchstones and powerful engines of charitable giving.</span>\n</p>\n\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"font-size:20px;\">We invite you to continue this legacy with us. By joining the Songbird Café and GameDay Café family, you become part of a tradition that celebrates music, community, and compassion — creating moments that resonate far beyond the stage and into the heart of our Midlands community.</span>\n</p>\n\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"font-size:20px;\"></span>\n</p>\n\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Below is a list of The Songbird Cafes’ and&nbsp;the GameDay Cafe’s, many singers, songwriters, producers, and everything else in between!</span>\n</p></div>",
